                  'Demarginalizing medieval Africa: Images, texts, and identity in early Solomonic Ethiopia (1270-1527)', grant ref. nos. AH/V002910/1 - 448410109</dc:publisher><dcterms:isPartOf rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu"/><dcterms:bibliographicCitation>PRS13683Asaph</dcterms:bibliographicCitation><dc:format>xml</dc:format><dc:language rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#language">en</dc:language><dc:language rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#language">gez</dc:language><dc:contributor>Alessandro Bausi</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>Jacopo Gnisci</dc:contributor><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/OldTestament"/><skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q43280403"/><foaf:gender>male</foaf:gender><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/ontology/pers"/><foaf:name xml:lang="en">Asaph</foaf:name><foaf:name xml:lang="gez">አሳፍ</foaf:name><crm:P4_has_time_span><crm:E52_Time-span><crm:P78_is_identified_by>Together with Heman, the grandson of the Israelite prophet Samuel (1 Chronicles 6:24, or 1 Chronicles 6:39 in non-Hebrew translations),
                      he and his male descendants were set aside by King David to worship God in song and music (1 Chronicles 15:16–17). He authored Psalm 50, and Psalms 73 to 83.
                    </crm:P78_is_identified_by></crm:E52_Time-span></crm:P4_has_time_span></rdf:Description></rdf:RDF>